## What was done

Phase 4 (runtime helpers) and Phase 5 (builtins) of the Second Bootstrap.

Phase 4: Ported 16 of 22 runtime helpers to Codex.Codex/Emit/X86_64Helpers.codex
(~1,300 lines). String, list, math helpers all working. 5 I/O helpers deferred to
Phase 7 (need rodata fixups + CCE tables).

Phase 5: Wired 30 pure-CCE builtins into emit-apply in X86_64.codex (~264 lines).
Inline builtins (text-length, list-at, negate, etc.) and helper-calling builtins
(text-replace, list-cons, etc.). I/O boundary builtins (print-line, read-file)
deferred to Phase 7.

Pingpong green throughout. Final state: 566KB ELF, 113MB Stage 1 HWM, 59s/59s.

## Next: Phase 6 — Escape Copy & Regions

This is the most intricate port in the backend. It's type-driven code generation,
not fixed assembly routines. The C# reference is in X86_64CodeGen.cs:
  - EmitRegion (lines 1305-1386): region entry/body/exit/escape
  - EmitEscapeCopy (lines 1388-1401): type dispatch wrapper
  - EmitEscapeCopyHelpers (lines 4177-4198): queue-draining generator
  - EmitFwdTableZero/Lookup/Insert (lines 4204-4328): hash table ops
  - EmitRecordEscapeHelper (lines 4390-4405): per-record-type helper
  - EmitListEscapeHelper (lines 4407-4477): per-list-type helper
  - EmitSumTypeEscapeHelper (lines 4479-4517): per-sum-type helper

Architecture:
  - Two-space heap: R10 = working space (temporaries), R15 = result space (escapes)
  - Forwarding hash table: 32K entries * 16 bytes = 512KB, linear probing
  - Table base stored in rodata global (m_fwdTableGlobalOffset)
  - Result space base stored in rodata global (m_resultBaseGlobalOffset)
  - IRRegion node triggers EmitRegion from emit-expr dispatch
  - Type-specific helpers queued lazily via GetOrQueueEscapeHelper
  - Helpers emitted at module end after all user functions

Rodata fixup blocker: Escape copy REQUIRES rodata fixups. The forwarding table
base and result-space base are stored in 8-byte rodata globals loaded via
MovRI64 + patch. This is the first feature forcing rodata fixup support into
the Codex codegen. CodegenState needs a rodata-fixups field.

## Key learnings (carry forward)

- CCE boundary principle: CCE is internal, Unicode is external. Conversion only
  at I/O boundaries (Phase 7).
- Circular dependency: builtins must live in same file as emit-expr.
- No comments in Codex. Prose is the explanation layer.
- Break deeply nested lets: max ~18 per function.
- Codex has no || operator. Use if/then True/else chains for boolean OR.
- Clean out/ of stale .codex/.elf/.cs files before building.
- Bare-metal memory: 128MB default, breakable to 512MB for linear growth.
